<ul class="panelbar">
    <li class="k-state-active">
        <span class="k-link k-state-selected">Question @Model?.Id</span>
        <div>
            <p>
                @Html.Raw(Model.H1OpenTag)
                You are configuring a Network Security Group (NSG). The default NSG rules are already in place.
                @Html.Raw(Model.H1CloseTag)
            </p>
            <p>
                @Html.Raw(Model.H2OpenTag)
                You need to configure the NSG to support only the following the types of traffic into the subnet from the Internet. 
                @Html.Raw(Model.H2CloseTag)
            </p>
            <p>
                * Remote Desktop Management
                <br />
                * Secured HTTPS traffic
                <br />
                * Unsecured HTTP traffic
            </p>
            <p>
                Which three ports should you configure in the NSG configuration? Each correct answer presents part of the solution.
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li class="k-state-active">
        Answers
        <div>
            <p>
                <ul class="fieldlist">
                    <li class="correct">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-checkbox">
                        <label class="k-checkbox-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            3389
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-checkbox">
                        <label class="k-checkbox-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            53
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li class="correct">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-checkbox">
                        <label class="k-checkbox-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            443
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li class="correct">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-checkbox">
                        <label class="k-checkbox-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            80
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-checkbox">
                        <label class="k-checkbox-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            21
                        </label>
                    </li>                   
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li>
        Explanation
        <div>
            <p>
                You should configure port 3389 for Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) connections, port 443 for Secured HTTP (HTTPS) connections, and port 80 for unsecured HTTP connections.
            </p>
            <p>
                You should not configure the NSG to support ports 21 or 53. Port 21 is for File Transfer Protocol (FTP) and port 53 is for Domain Name System (DNS).
            </p>
            <p>
                The default NSG rules are already set so there is no requirement to configure anything beyond these rules.
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li>
        References
        <div>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/azurerm.network/new-azurermnetworksecurityruleconfig" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">New-AzureRMNetworkSecurityRuleConfig</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/azurerm.network/new-azurermnetworksecuritygroup" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">New-AzureRMNetworkSecurityGroup</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/windows/it-pro/windows-2000-server/cc959828(v=technet.10)" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Port Assignments for Well Known Ports</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
</ul>